<subSubSection id="D4A6E012824C0172CC4B4BECABDF8FA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="notes">
<paragraph id="A24CE508D929886247B9D3F550BB7060" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DCDA1E07C4D9169F592BDE1677FF5E77" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName id="2147B274430AF98FC0DC60A8CDCBCAD6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pogostemon dielsianus" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dielsianus">
<emphasis id="FC1E33113BE799730589C8C7CB1FAD08" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Pogostemon dielsianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1B37A73DD3BCA88686B6538498AC79AE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. elsholtzioides" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="elsholtzioides">
<emphasis id="F06945E11E3DEC96DE077E7AC24E49C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. elsholtzioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2E8475A72F9BA21E1BC95532A186F7A2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. griffithii" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="griffithii">
<emphasis id="2EDFCA9BB96F9543FB423E8B3D9CB472" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. griffithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having lanceolate leaves. However, 
<taxonomicName id="E0C60915B43111CD81445764BAB6309B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. dielsianus" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="dielsianus">
<emphasis id="217061A0A7CD67871EF594FEA773072E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. dielsianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="CB6B8E99ADB65913D07A3069ABE99266" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. elsholtzioides" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="elsholtzioides">
<emphasis id="D217B0C20B4585494D0FFB362616EF8D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. elsholtzioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="82FD6B7518643EC50CD337D46F169F24" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. griffithii" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="griffithii">
<emphasis id="9AE3538D25797D5B325F4A585B5C6CC4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. griffithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its longer and tubular calyx, smaller ratio of the length of calyx teeth and calyx tube and longer corolla, filament and style (Table 
<tableCitation id="A300148504E15B8E283C06AB896C8ED6" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T2" captionText="Table 2. Morphological comparison between Pogostemon dielsianus and its morphologically similar species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/548984BD11452551F2B5BF88970362B9" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" tableUuid="548984BD11452551F2B5BF88970362B9">2</tableCitation>
). In addition, the geographical distribution of these three species is also different in that 
<taxonomicName id="5035BC925E732D74A8DA383A74243524" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. dielsianus" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="dielsianus">
<emphasis id="EB709C9B16D82F6332B2DC1B727AA0BC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. dielsianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to NW Yunnan, China, 
<taxonomicName id="E8F8982C8383DABA8B61F30A97BF0FED" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. elsholtzioides" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="elsholtzioides">
<emphasis id="796BFF319D660E6B035FB1385F90FD4E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. elsholtzioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in the Himalayan regions (Bhutan, India, and SE Xizang, China), and 
<taxonomicName id="2A3F23B5F6F56C1A90E370C14EBDE873" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. griffithii" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="griffithii">
<emphasis id="E08F0213D27818A60DF2784FE70DACA2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">P. griffithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Myanmar (
<bibRefCitation id="AEC64053A3E3577E753DA04C11D74E9F" author="Bhatti, GR" journalOrPublisher="London (Botany)" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="77 - 147" refId="B2" refString="Bhatti, GR, Ingrouille, M, 1997. Systematics of Pogostemon (Labiatae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum. London (Botany) 27 (2): 77 - 147" title="Systematics of Pogostemon (Labiatae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum." volume="27" year="1997">Bhatti and Ingrouille 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="687D09F065789BD96D2396365EBC3CB0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.200.1.1" author="Yao, G" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 67" refId="B28" refString="Yao, G, Deng, YF, Ge, XJ, 2015. A taxonomic revision of Pogostemon (Lamiaceae) from China. Phytotaxa 200 (1): 1 - 67, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.200.1.1" title="A taxonomic revision of Pogostemon (Lamiaceae) from China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.200.1.1" volume="200" year="2015">Yao et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F94E1C29A79B543229D524949F9EA3F4" author="Yao, G" journalOrPublisher="Re dai ya re dai zhi wu xue bao [Journal of tropical and subtropical botany]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" pagination="553 - 555" refId="B27" refString="Yao, G, Ge, XJ, 2018. Pogostemon chinensis (Lamiaceae), a newly recorded species from India. Re dai ya re dai zhi wu xue bao [Journal of tropical and subtropical botany] 26 (5): 553 - 555" title="Pogostemon chinensis (Lamiaceae), a newly recorded species from India." volume="26" year="2018">Yao and Ge 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
